carrying precious stones which make sound, and cool sandal-wood. Viṭaivāy where the fragrant water comes and descendsThe water is the floods in the rivulet Pāṇtavāy which is mentioned in the veṇpā by Aiyaṭikaḷ Kāṭavar Kōṉ nāyaṉār quoted before.
Civaṉ who consumed the poison which rose in the roaring ocean, just like nectar;
people say is the place where Civaṉ who has the colour of fire and a caṭai on which the Kaṅkai with waves, stays.
